Coffee Exports From Mexico Increased 53% in May, Amecafe Says

-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-06-10T15:36:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/coffee-exports-from-mexico-increased-53-in-may-amecafe-says.html
Mexico ’s coffee exports rose 53
percent in May, according to figures from the country’s coffee
association, known as Amecafe.  Shipments climbed to 380,159 bags from 247,199 bags a year
earlier, Amecafe said in an e-mailed statement today. Exports
for the season that started Oct. 1 fell 5.6 percent to 1.75
million bags.  Mexico’s coffee production in the current season is
estimated at 4 million bags, Rodolfo Trampe Taubert, the
association’s executive coordinator, said March 31.  A bag of coffee weighs 60 kilograms (132 pounds).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isis Almeida in London at 
 ialmeida3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
